@page "/party-management"

<PageTitle>Party Management - D&D Combat Tracker</PageTitle>

<h1>Party Management</h1>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
    <strong>Coming Soon!</strong> This page will allow you to create, edit, and manage your adventuring party.
</div>

<div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3>Features</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Add and remove party members</li>
            <li>Track character stats (HP, AC, Initiative Modifier)</li>
            <li>Manage character classes and levels</li>
            <li>Store notes and passive perception</li>
            <li>Support for multiple party profiles</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3>Planned Functionality</h3>
        <p>The Party Management system will allow you to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Create persistent party data using Entity Framework Core</li>
            <li>Quickly load parties into combat encounters</li>
            <li>Edit character information between sessions</li>
            <li>Export and import party data</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to Home</a>
</div>
